gomodel:SYNGO_297  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Prohibitin (as well as Prohibitin-2) has no detectable transmembrane domain, however, it copurifies with protein fractions highly enriched in docked synaptic vesicles.. Experimental description: To isolate docking complexes from rat brain, we first prepared synaptosomes and subjected them to limited proteolysis to dissociate pre- and postsynaptic membranes (Figure 1A). p. 286" ;
